         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">June 6th, 1862. ¶ Dear Dr. Wills, ¶  ¶ Once more I wish you a most cordial good-bye, and trust that in the circle of your family you will feel some consolation for the dreadful bereavement which has b...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">62.06.06d</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Wills</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">Letter not found. For the text given here, see Wills (1863), p. 363 (B63.01.05).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>June 6th, 1862.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Dr. Wills,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Once more I wish you a most cordial good-bye, and trust that in the circle of your family you will feel some consolation for the dreadful bereavement which has befallen you in the loss of your son.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">William Wills left Sydney per <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Cairngorm</seg> for England on 18 June 1862 (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Sydney morning herald</seg>, 21 June 1862, p. 8), having arrived from Melbourne on 16 June (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Empire</seg> (Sydney), 16 June 1862, p. 4).</p>
               </note> May it alleviate your affliction to some small extent, to remember that your son has gained by the sacrifice of his precious life a world-wide fame, and an appreciation which will remain unobliterated throughout all ages.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With the deepest solicitude for your health and happiness, I remain, my very dear Dr. Wills,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Your attached friend,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
      </body>
